{
  "texts": [
    "LDA is a generative probabilistic model that captures the important intra-word/document statistical structure via a mixing distribution.",
    "LDA assumes that each document is associated with a topic distribution.",
    "LDA has been applied successfully to various domain, however, the performance is inconsistent especially when applied to short text (Ogunleye et al. 2023).",
    "These conventional TM techniques encounter data sparsity problem which is prevalent in short text.",
    "Based on this background, Yan et al. (2013) proposed biterm topic model (BTM) to solve the issue of data sparsity in short text."
  ]
}